| Plot                    = After being saved by the [[Guardians of the Galaxy (Earth-TRN971)|Guardians of the Galaxy]], the [[Nova Corps (Earth-TRN971)|Nova Corps]], now aware of [[Earth]] sent the [[Xandarian Chamber Orchestra (Earth-TRN971)|Xandarian Chamber Orchestra]] to its cultural epicenter, [[Epcot]], in order to teach a [[Earth-1218#Residents|crowd of terrans]] about their culture through music.

Aware of this, [[Peter Quill (Earth-TRN971)|Star-Lord]] and [[Gamora (Earth-TRN971)|Gamora]] go to Epcot, in order to save the galaxy from "bad music". With help from [[Groot (Earth-TRN971)|Groot]], aboard the ''[[Benatar]]'', Star-Lord sends tunes from his [[Awesome Mix]] to the Orchestra's headsets. Star-Lord helps the orchestra play 4 different songs, while Gamora reiterates to him that "bad music" is not a serious emergency that warrants their presence. Star-Lord concedes, and begins to leave after the fourth song, but the Orchestra choose to play {{WP|The Jackson 5}}'s {{WP|I Want You Back|"I Want You Back"}} without his help. The Guardians stay to watch, but Groot alerts them that a fleet of [[Sovereign Drone Ships]] is attacking the Benatar. The two leave, but Star-Lord tells the Orchestra to choose a new name if they want to become a truly great cover band, and the Orchestra takes the name "The Star-Lords" in his honor, before finishing their song.

