| Notes                   = * The stage show attraction includes covers of five classic rock song including:
** {{WP|Hooked on a Feeling|"Hooked on a Feeling"}} by {{WP|Blue Swede}}
** {{WP|Come and Get Your Love|"Come and Get Your Love"}} by {{WP|Redbone (band)|Redbone}}
** {{WP|Hit Me with Your Best Shot|"Hit Me With Your Best Shot"}} by {{WP|Pat Benatar}}
** {{WP|Don’t Stop Me Now|"Don't Stop Me Now"}} by {{WP|Queen (band)|Queen}}
** {{WP|I Want You Back|"I Want You Back"}} by {{WP|The Jackson 5}}
* Although most songs featured in this stage show were selected from [[Awesome Mix Vol. 1]] and [[Awesome Mix Vol. 2]], neither {{WP|Hit Me with Your Best Shot|"Hit Me With Your Best Shot"}} by {{WP|Pat Benatar}} nor {{WP|Don’t Stop Me Now|"Don’t Stop Me Now"}} by {{WP|Queen (band)|Queen}} were part of the [[Earth-199999|Marvel Cinematic Universe]] version of these compilations.
[[File:Guardians of the Galaxy - Awesome Mix Live! 002.jpg|300px|right|thumb|The marquee advertising the Guardians of the Galaxy – Awesome Mix Live! showtimes at the American Gardens Theatre by the Shore]]
* This attraction operated as a stage show at the American Gardens Theatre in the American Adventure Pavilion in [[Disney World|Epcot]]'s World Showcase.<ref name="returning">{{cite web|url=https://disneyparks.disney.go.com/blog/2019/06/guardians-of-the-galaxy-awesome-mix-live-returns-to-epcot/|title=‘Guardians of the Galaxy – Awesome Mix Live!’ Returns to Epcot|work=Disney Parks Blog|first=Thomas|last=Smith|date=14 June 2019|accessdate=17 Feb 2021}}</ref>
* This stage show attraction ran from June 9th through August 19th, 2018. The stage show later returned from June 14th to August 18th, 2019.<ref name="returning"/>
* Despite looking like the [[Earth-199999]] ship, the ''[[Milano]]'', the Guardians' ship is referred to as the ''[[Benatar]]'' by [[Gamora]].

| Trivia                  = * This is the second Disney Theme Park attraction inspired by the [[Guardians of the Galaxy]], with the first being [[Guardians of the Galaxy - Mission: BREAKOUT!]] in {{WP|Disney California Adventure}} which opened on May 27, 2017.

